content: G'day everyone. Just jumping on to say hello. I'm currently a fairly beginner Rust programmer, and I'm trying to improve my understanding of the language by trying to contribute to some of the easy issues.

Hi everyone! I’m Freddie, a CS undergrad. I’ve been coding in Rust for a while now but finally decided I wanted to contribute to the community and help out. I’m interested in anything networks/distributed systems as well as high performance stuff (done some stuff in AVX and optimisation). If anyone has anything in those areas I’d love to help out and contribute to it :)
Hi @Freddie Brown! We got #t-compiler/performance for compiler performance.
@bjorn3 thanks for the suggestion, I’ll have a look!
